<h2>Sellers FAQ</h2>
<dl>
    <dt>
        What property types can I sell on Nationwide?
    </dt>
    <dd>
        Residential & Commercial investment properties. Can be sold individually or in a pool of homes. Our main focus is Turn-Key cash-flowing residential.
    </dd>
    <dt>
        What is the cost to list my properties on Nationwide?
    </dt>
    <dd>
        Property listings on Nationwide is free for agents, brokers and the property owner. All fees are paid by the buyer.
    </dd>
    <dt>
        What is the cost to buy and sell on Nationwide?
    </dt>
    <dd>
        If you are buying a property on Nationwide you will pay a monthly User account fee to have access to our database and with the close of each property you will pay a buyers fee.
    </dd>
    <dt>
        What is the buyer agents commission?
    </dt>
    <dd>
        The commission is determined by the seller in the listing contract. The minimum commission is 6% to be split by both Agents. Seller may offer a higher commission.
    </dd>
    <dt>
        How do I add our property listings?
    </dt>
    <dd>
        First create a sellers account. Second you can choose between an automatic upload using our proprietary software integration with your property software tool OR manual upload using .csv.
    </dd>
    <dt>
        Why Nationwide
    </dt>
    <dd>
        <ul>
            <li>Free for the seller and his agent or broker</li>
            <li>The agent remains the agent and primary contact</li>
            <li>The designated agent and/or seller are in control with the review and approval process</li>
            <li>Your properties are marketed by our website as well as our many partner sites</li>
        </ul>
    </dd>
</dl>
